Protesters demonstrate in Ogulagha community (also known as Gulani) demanding the restoration of the scrapped Nigerian Maritime University (NMU) at Okerenkoko, Warri South West Local Government Area.
Unidentified gunmen abduct traditional ruler in Isoko South Local Government Area.
"Economic vandals" destroy oil pipelines with bombs in several locations in Brass LGA over two days.
Fulanis attack another group of Fulanis land in Kuje. One death reported.

At least five members of the Civilian Joint Task Force were killed while four others sustained critical injuries when a Toyota Hilux patrol vehicle rammed into landmines/ Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs) in Buma, Kaga LGA suspected to have been planted by members of Boko Haram.
Nigerian forces clash with suspected members of Boko Haram in Maiduguri on 30/01. No reported casualties.

Boko Haram attacks Dalori village on 30/01 killing many. Many of the dead were children who had been burnt alive. The attack occurred during the evening hours. The death toll was raised to 101 over the course of the week (The Guardian).
A bloody conflict between suspected Fulani herdsmen and Agatu farmers at Ega Adapti Island in Agstu Local Government Area of Benue State claimed 10 lives.
Students protested in front of City Hall to demand subsidies.
Workers at Youssou Mbargane Diop hospital went on strike to oppose structural policies, paralyzing many services.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: SUTRAIL: Single Union of Rail Workers
SOURCE: Agence de Presse Senegalaise; Sud Quotidien
NOTES: Transrail workers went on strike to protest delays in salaries, paralyzing the small commuter train system.
Students, teachers and civil society organizations marched to advocate for girls' rights.
Unidentified group set fire to Dabo High School, causing major damage. A guard caught one of the perpetrators and handed him over to police.
Around 100 demonstrators from an anti-gay coalition protested against the release of accused homosexuals. Police dispersed protesters and arrested 11 because the protest was unauthorized.
Local government workers marched to demand payment of salaries.
Police arrested nearly 900 people in a two-day operation in Dakar and Thies in an effort to prevent potential terror attacks. Soldiers stationed on roads and in buildings and carry out searches.
Protesters marched against the recent publication by Jeune Afrique of a controversial cartoon depicting a Mouride religious leader.

Youth protested Ebola restrictions that have halted market activity in Barmoi Luma in Kambia district. At least eight people were injured, including with bullet wounds, as demonstrators allegedly burned down a police station and police fired tear gas to disperse them. 18 youths were arrested.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: Muslim Group (Sierra Leone); Christian Group (Sierra Leone)
NOTES: Sierra Leone's Muslim and Christian leaders marched to parliament in Freetown to protest against a controversial draft law on abortion.
Angry youth pelted stones at Fire Forces for their alleged delay in responding to stress calls as a fire was engulfing a family's house Siaka Stevens Street.

Two clan militias from Gaal Jecel and Jajeele sub-clans clashed in the vicinity of Buq-Goosaar (50km SW of Beled Weyne) in the morning of 01/01. At least seven combatants from both sides were killed in the clash which lasted for several hours.
In the wake of the chaos caused by two groups of warring clan militias, al Shabaab took over Buq Koosaar without a fight.

Scuffles broke out between two youth groups from Habar Yonis and Dhulbahante sub-clans in Daalo neighbourhood (Ceerigaabo) on 01/01 following a dispute over territorial control. Ceerigaabo police intervened, shot in the air and arrested 5 people from both sides.
Al Shabaab attacked a Heliwa police station the evening of 01/01. The police officers responded, killing three of the attackers and capturing one.
Unidentified assassins shoot and kill a Turkish national outside a mosque in Hodan District on 01/01. The reason for the targeting is not known.

Al Shabaab fighters fired at least six projectiles (SPG9 OR B10) against Xalane Base (Waberi District) in the early morning of 01/01. Four of them landed in an open ground and two landed in the sea. The rounds were probably fired from Jazeera side. No injuries reported.

The employees of Somaliland citizenship registration demonstrated in front of the mayor's office in Borama in 02/01 over unpaid salaries. The employees said that they have closed the office and will remain so until the dispute is resolved.

Two people reportedly died, one of them the suicide bomber in an explosion that happened at a restaurant near the National Theatre in Mogadishu on 2 January. It is reported that four other people were injured in the explosion. Some of the injured work for the Somali government and the rest are civilians who were taking tea at the restaurant. There was no immediate claim of responsibility but officials will likely blame the Al-Shabaab group.

Somali National Army (SNA) and local clan militia fought in Baraawe in the morning of 03/01 over unknown reasons. The fighting lasted almost one hour after which the military forces overpowered the local militia. Three combatants from the militia were confirmed dead while three SNA soldiers were injured in the fighting. The situation is calm (at the time of this report) and there is a possibility of recurrence of the clashes.

A group of Borama Town residents staged demonstrations on 03/01 following the recent strike by the employees of Somaliland citizen registration office in Borama. The demonstrators urged the government to intervene and resolve the issue.

Local media reported that two dead bodies of traders were found in the vicinity of Ceel Shiil (3km W of Ceel Buur) in the morning of 03/01. Locals confirmed that the victims were Ceel Shiil villagers. Al Shabaab are believed to be responsible (Somali Dhacdo). The two were likely targeted for regularly conducting business with SNG soldiers.

Local taxi drivers staged a massive demonstration in front of the local municipality and the main tarmac road, halting businesses and traffic movements in Garowe in the morning of 03/01. The protest came after government banned local taxis to ferry Khat sellers to and from the western checkpoint on suspicion of smuggling alcohol. Garowe police arrested some of the protestors.
Unidentified gunmen have reportedly killed a civilian while driving a luxury car in Hodan District on 03/01. It is not clear if the victim was a civilian or government official.

Unidentified men armed with pistols shot and severely injured a civilian man in CC neighbourhood (Karaan District) in the evening of 03/01. The motive of the attack is unknown and perpetrators escaped.
Local militias (not identified) and al Shabaab fighters briefly clashed in Moor Eri (approx. 35km S of Maxaas) on 03/01. No casualties were reported.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters beheaded a traditional elder in Rabdhure Town in the night of 03/01. The elder previously spoke very critical about the insecurity of the town which is created by al Shabaab.

A group of suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against SNGF position in Carbiska settlement (5km SE of Afgooye) on 04/01. After a brief exchange of gun-fire, al Shabaab fighters withdrew. No casualties were reported.

Ceerigaabo local government supported by the police destroyed small kiosks constructed illegally at the central grocery market in Ceerigaabo on 04/01. A group of kiosk owners attempted to stop the operations but two of them were arrested including a kiosk owner from Habar Yonis/Mohamud Hamud sub-clan who stabbed and injured one of the local government staff from Habar-Jeclo/Basan Buur sub-clan during the operations.

Police reports indicate that armed men from Majeerten/Dishishe sub-clan shot and killed two people and injured another over land dispute in Xange area near Dalwayn Village (83km N of Qardo) on the evening of  04/01. The victims hail from Majeerten/Osman Mohamud sub-clan and were searching for gold on the dispute land when the incident happened.The perpetrators escaped. The killing caused tension in the area.

Puntland customs police briefly exchanged gunfire with militias from Galmudug in the vicinity of Darxumo Market (Green line) in Galkacyo in the morning of 04/01 over taxation dispute. Stray bullets reportedly killed a businessman from Dir clan and injured another civilian. No other casualties were reported and the situation is calm.

At least one person was killed and another injured when unidentified armed assailants attacked an apartment housing Turkish nationals near Mogadishu's main airport in Hamar Jabjab. The attack occurred during the nighttime hours of 04/01. Perpetrators not known.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: A RCIED targeted AMISOM/KDF convoy heading to Afmadow on its way from Dhoobley in Hawina (approx. 90km SW of Afmadow) in the morning of 04/01. One vehicle was damaged and three KDF soldiers were injured.

Two groups of SNGF briefly exchanged gunfire after one group stopped a vehicle with SNGF on security operation at Zobe junction (Hodan District) and they became suspicious of each other on 04/01. No casualties were reported.

Suspected Dhulbahante gunmen opened fire at a herd of camels belonging to Habarjeclo/Ahmed Farah sub-clan in the vicinity of Qocondhaale near Horufadhi Village (39km N of Buuhoodle) on 04/01. The camels were fetching water at the time of the incident. The gunmen destroyed jerry-cans and reportedly sexually assaulted a woman who was herding the camels before escaping from the area. The motive of the incident remains unknown. The incident comes one day after elders from Dhulbahante/Cigaal Naaleeye sub-clan and Habarjeclo/Ahmed Farah sub-clan reached peace agreement in Meygaagle Village.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Ethiopia)
NOTES: IED explosion targeted AMISOM/ENDF convoy in Leego (48km SE of Buur Hakaba) in the afternoon of 04/01. The explosion was followed by a brief armed clash which lasted for 30 minutes. Causalities could not be confirmed.

Unidentified perpetrators driving in a SURV vehicle tried to assassinate a Turkish national outside MIA in the late hours of 04/01. SNGF and his private security guards engaged the attackers in a gun-battle before they withdrew. Initial reports indicate that one of the attackers was killed and one security guard got injured.

Al Shabaab fighters clashed with SNG forces in Warmahan (31km NW of Afgooye) in the early morning of 04/01. Initial reports indicate that al Shabaab fighters overrun the town and confiscated a technical from SNGF while SNG forces retreated to Afgooye. The SNG forces reportedly suffered at least 8 fatalities and five injuries.
Following the capture of War Maxan by al Shabaab forces, government forces were able to recapture the village later the same afternoon. Additional casualties not known.

Two unidentified perpetrators armed with pistols shot and severely injured a man in Biyo Daaga (Yaaqshiid District) in the morning of 04/01. The motive is unknown but reports suggest that the victim was working with the government forces. The perpetrators managed to escape.
Al Shabaab fighters attack SNG forces in Ceel Shiil Village (3km SW of Ceel Buur) on 04/01. No causalities reported.

SNGF attacked Aw Misigey (approx. 23km NE of Buur-Hakaba). They were supported by helicopters departing from Wanla Weyn District in Lower Shabelle. First reports indicate that sixteen al Shabaab fighters including their commander were killed and one managed to escape.

A device believed to be an UXO exploded in the vicinity of Bali Busle Village (145km S of Laas- Qoray) on 05/01, killing two boys and seriously injuring another. The boys were brothers and hail from Warsangeli sub-clan. The victims were herding goats when the incident happened. The device is believed to have been planted in the area during the civil war era.

Traders protested against new taxes imposed by Puntland government on imported goods at the port of Bosasso in the morning of 05/01. The traders refused to collect their goods from the port as result of the new tax tariff.
Somali forces have killed "several" Al-Shabab fighters in fighting against the group in southwestern Somalia town of Buurhakaba. No reported soldier dead.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: AMISOM-Somali forces overtake Towfiq village near the central town of Gal'ad during a military offensive in the area. Causalities, if any, were left unreported.

A group of gunmen from Mareehan/Wagardhac sub-clan reportedly opened fire and carjacked a Toyota Mark II (2) car belonging to Majeerteen/Isse Mohamud sub-clan in the vicinity of Garsoor neighbourhood (Galkacyo North) in the evening of 05/01.
Suspected al Shabaab fighter attacked a SNGF base located near Ivo S Company on 05/01. Both sides exchanged gun fire before the attackers withdrew. No casualties were reported.
Unknown perpetrators hurled a hand grenade against SNG forces on foot patrol on 05/01. The grenade landed at an empty space and exploded causing no casualties. The perpetrators managed to escape.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: A powerful explosion hit a Kenyan convoy passing the road linking Dhooblay district and Taabto area in Lower Jubba. The blast killed a Kenyan commander and about 10 of his escorts, and forced the convoy to be stranded at the scene of the attack for several hours.
A former al Shabaab commander, who defected in 2015, is shot and killed on 06/01 in Berdera by suspected al Shabaab.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters shot and killed a SNG soldier in Buulo Mareer Village (27 KM SW of Marka) on 06/01. Other SNGF who were rushing to the scene opened fire killing two civilian by-standers, presumably without intention. Perpetrators managed to escape.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters carried out a hit and run attack against SNGF base in Goof Gaduud Village (30km NW of Baidoa) on 06/01. Four soldiers were killed and four others were injured. Three civilians were also injured in the clash.

Two groups of suspected al Shabaab fighters carried out coordinated attacks on SNGP and NISA troops position in Biyo Degaanka and Abdiwayel Cinema neighbourhoods on 06/01. No casualties were reported and attackers withdrew.

Two groups of SNGF clashed in Zona K neighbourhood on 06/01. One Group was forcefully on eviction and demolishing operation but was engaged by the other SNGF group who inhabit the area. Two civilians were killed and the two groups were mediated by AMISOM/SNGF.

SNG police attacked two SNGF who set up an illegal check-point at Jambaluul (6km NE of Afgooye) on 06/01. The forces arrested the two soldiers, manning the illegal check-point and no casualties were reported.
Suspected al Shabaab execute a 90-year-old man in Rab Dhuure district on 06/01. The killing caused area SNG forces to respond, killing four of the suspected responsible.
Suspected al Shabaab execute a 90-year-old man in Rab Dhuure district (exact location not known) on 06/01. The killing caused area SNG forces to respond, killing four of the suspected responsible.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against a NISA outpost in Caymiska neighbourhood on 06/01. Both sides exchanged heavy gunfire that lasted for around 15 minutes before attackers withdrew. No casualties were reported.
Unidentified attackers hurled a hand grenade against a house in Beled Xawo where SNG police were staying on 06/01. Causalities, injuries no reported.

An IED exploded in Haween Village (18km NW of Baidoa) targeting a lorry deploying troops from Baidoa town to Goof Gaduud Burey Village in the morning of 07/01. The IED explosion injured eleven soldiers who are now receiving medical assistance in Baidoa Hospital.

Al Shabaab fighters targeted an ISWA reinforcement convoy with an IED near Sanilow Village (25km NW of Baidoa) on 07/01. Immediately after the explosion an armed clash between ISWA and al Shabaab fighters erupted. Two ISWA soldiers were killed and four others were injured. Casualties on al Shabaab side are not known.

Unknown perpetrators launched a mortar attack from an unknown location targeting most likely Villa Somalia on 07/01. First reports indicate that all rounds fell in civilian neighbourhoods killing two people. Al Shabaab later claimed responsibility for the attack.

At least 12 people were killed and 25 others were wounded in a battle between al Shabaab fighters against Somali government troops and South West Administration forces in the village of Goofguduud on 08/01.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: Suspected al Shabaab detonate a roadside bomb targeting a AMISOM convoy in the Shalaamboot region. The explosion caused damage to the vehicle.

Hundreds of Galkacyo (South) residents staged in a peaceful demonstration against the Speaker of the Somali parliament following his visit to Dhusamareeb in the morning of 08/01. The speaker together with other parliamentarians visited Dhusamareeb on 06/01 to meet with leaders of ASWJ on a peace mission to de-escalate the political tension with Galmudug State. The protest took place in Gaalkacyo.

A group of Bossaso residents hailing from Majerteen/Dashiishe sub-clan staged a demonstration in Bossaso in the morning of 08/01 in protest against Puntland president's speech accusing him of siding with their opponent (Osman Mohamud). The president's speech was calling for peaceful coexistence between the two sub-clan following a land dispute. The protest turned to violent while police at the scene responded with live bullets. One person was killed while another two others were injured.

Unidentified attackers armed with knives and other crude weapons reportedly assaulted a freelance journalist in Buuhoodle on 08/01. The motive behind the attack is currently unknown. The perpetrators escape while the victim was later admitted to Manhal Hospital in Laas Caanood.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighters conducted a hit and run attack against AMISOM/KDF contingent base in Badhaadhe town on 09/01.The sides briefly clashed for about 10 minutes after the attackers withdrew. The Kenya Daily reported the SNG forces reported with gunfire, killing 19 of the attackers.
Al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against ISWA forces based in the outskirt of Baidoa town in night of 09/01. No casualties were reported from both sides.

Two groups of farmers hailing from two sub-clans of Gadabuursi clashed using sticks and stones on 09/01 over dispute on farm irrigation in Qodax Village (22km SE of Borama. Local elders intervened and managed to separate the two groups. No casualties were reported.

Gunmen dressed in Somali military uniform have opened fire on a civilian bus in Warsheekh town of middle Shabelle region, killing one person and injuring 5 others. The reason of the attack is not known.

Two groups of SNG forces clashed in Bardheere police station in the afternoon of 10/01. The clash reportedly lasted for several hours. Reports indicate that the fighting was triggered following the murder of a former al Shabaab defector on 06/01 who was part of SNG forces in Bardheere. A soldier was killed during the fighting while unspecified number of soldiers were injured as well as a civilian.

Gunmen from Warsangeli/Reer Haji sub-clan open fire against a convoy of five lorries transporting goods from Bossaso to Ceerigaabo and Ceel-Afwayn in the vicinity of Bali Busle village (145km S of Laas-Qoray) in the night of 10/01. The attackers exchanged fire with gunmen onboard of the lorries. Reports indicate that the attacked vehicles three belongs to Habar-Jeclo while the other two belongs Warsangeli and apparently the attackers were targeting vehicles of Habar-Jeclo in a revenge for a boat belonging to the attackers sub-clan seized by Somaliland coastal guards after the forces rescued some illegal Ethiopian immigrants. Following the shootout a civilian bystander from the attacker's sub-clan was injured and later succumbed to his injuries. At the time of reporting all the five vehicles were being held in Bali Busle pending investigation of who killed the deceased man while the victim of the relatives refused to bury the body until the real perpetrator is identified.
One soldier is dead and two others wounded when unidentified attackers hurled a pair of grenades at their location near an Afgooye orphanage.

Unidentified attackers hurled simultaneously two hand grenade against SNG police based in the former Orphanage centre in Hawo Tako neighbourhood (Afgooye) in the evening of 10/01. The perpetrators escaped. No casualties were reported.

Suspected magnetic IED planted in a car detonated in Manaboliyo Junction (Shibis District) in the morning of10/01. A government official was killed while another one was injured. No one has claimed the responsibility for the attack.
Al Shabaab attacks the car of an army colonel in Shibis on 10/01, killing him. The explosive was detonated remotely.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters conducted a hit and run attack against SNG position in Carbiska (5km E of Afgooye) on 10/01. No reported causalities.

An IED targeted a vehicle belonging to a businessman and well-known farmer in Hawo Tako neighbourhood (Afgooye) in the afternoon of 11/01. The businessman was killed while two other people were injured in the explosion.

Hundreds of people held a demonstration in Warta Nabadda (Wardhiigleey) district, Banaadir region [Mogadishu], in support of peace in Mogadishu and the elimination of Al Shabaab. They carried placards stating their feelings.

Unidentified gunmen shot and killed the principal of Al-Cayn secondary school and a lecturer of Ganane University (Sh. Mohamed Cadow Hilowle) from Rahanweyn/Geledle sub-clan and inured two of his children in Baidoa in the night of 11/01. The motive behind the killing us currently unclear. Reports indicate that the victim previously used to support al Shabaab fighters.
Unidentified gunmen shot and killed a prominent businessman in Afgooye on 11/01.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters conducted a hit and run attack against SNG forces Rimaygacmeed (6km SW of Afgooye) on 11/01. No causalities reported.

Garowe local government supported by police officers demolished illegally constructed small kiosks along Sodanka road on 12/01. A group of kiosk owners tried to stop the operation and in the process a kiosk owner from Issa Mohamud stabbed and injured a local municipal officer from Majerteen/Biciidyahan. The police arrested seven people including the perpetrator who stabbed the officer.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters attacked SNG forces based in Danow village (16km NW of Marka) on 12/01.

A large number of Somaliland troops were reportedly deployed in Bali-Hadhac (62km NE of Buuhoodle) on 13/01. The motive behind the fresh deployment is currently unclear however, some reports suggest that the deployment is due to political tensions in the region and the mobilization of forming new regional state comprises of Dhulbahante and Warsangeli lands. The forces were reportedly dispatched to prevent Khatumo president of holding any meetings in Buuhoodle district. Further reports suggest that the forces proceed to Bali Cad village (51km SE of Buuhoodle) along Somalia Ethiopia border and later takeover of the village in the morning of 14/01. The village is current Khatumo headquarter, however no armed clash was reported.

Al Shabaab fighters reportedly abducted another al Shabaab fighter in the vicinity of Idale village (56km SW of Baidoa) in the morning of 13/01 while heading towards Baidoa. Reports indicate that the al Shabaab fighters suspected the member of being spy for SNG forces.

A group of youth gangs armed with clubs reportedly assaulted and looted hawkers of Ethiopian nationals in Tuurta neighbourhood (Burco) on 13/01 for allegedly relating the Ethiopian nationals to a recent incident where a man from Ethiopia was accused of being a man-eater after he allegedly killed a young girl near Burco. Elders intervened and stopped the youth gangs from robbing the vendors.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attacked against AMISOM/KDF contingent base in Kolbiyow Village (38km SW of Badhaadhe) in the evening of 13/01.The clash lasted for about 15 minutes and both sides used light weapons before the attackers withdrew. No casualties were reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: AMISOM/KDF contingent attacked using artillery and mortar fire against a group of al Shabaab fighters spotted near Bula Gaduud Village (30km NE of Kismaayo) in the evening of 13/01.The attack lasted for about three hours and no casualties were reported from al Shabaab side so far.
Iranian aid agency was looted in Mogadishu by some locals on 13/01 after Somalia cut its diplomatic relations with Iran.

Two groups of SNG forces clashed in Ex-control Afgooye (Dharkenleey District) in the night of 14/01. The exact reason behind the cause of the clash is currently unclear, however there are two accounts; one of the version suggest that a group of SNG forces who were base at the residential house of one of the SNG military commanders Col. Hassan Mohamed clashed within themselves while the other version suggest that a group of SNG forces attacked a SNG military base in the area where the fighting lasted for several hours. Unspecified number of soldiers were killed while several other were injured.

Al Shabaab fighters attacked SNG forces based in Ceel-Shil village (3km SW of Ceel Buur) on 14/01. Reports indicate that al Shabaab fighters used rocket propelled grenades and heavy machine guns which lasted for several hours however, according to media reports the attackers were repulsed back. At least nine al Shabaab fighters and a SNG soldier were killed in the clash while unspecified numbers from both sides were injured. Conflicting report: Somali Memo reported al Shabaab took over the town.
Somali forces shoot and kill four members of al Shabaab during a security operation in Maxaas.

A RCIED planted on a road side exploded in front of a restaurant in Bardaale (55km NW of Baidoa) in the evening of 14/01. A SNG soldier and refugee returnee from Dadaab camp were killed while two other civilians were injured. Perpetrators not known.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: A member of AMISOM kills a civilian in Golweyn for unknown reason.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters attacked SNG base in Cumar Beere (9km NW of Afgooye) on 14/01. No reported causalities. SNG forces vacated the village as result of the attack. It is not clear if al Shabaab took control of the village following the attack.

Gunmen hailing from Dir briefly exchanged gunfire with armed men collecting stones at quarry site hailing from Habar Gidir/Sa'ad sub-clan in near Hiiraan one IDP camp in Galkacyo south on 14/01. A stray bullet reportedly killed a woman in the IDP camp.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighters conducted a complex attack against AMISOM/KDF contingent base in Cell Cadde Village (50km SW of Garbahaarey) in the morning of 15/01. The early morning attack started with a vehicle loaded with explosive devices driven by a suicide bomber to open up the access gate while other al Shabaab fighters fought their way inside to the base. Initial information suggest that heavily armed al Shabaab fighters engaged fiercest fighting with Kenyan Defence Forces which lasted for several hours. Al Shabaab spokesman for military operation Sheikh Abdiaziz Abu-muscab, said that their fighters have captured the base and seized heavy military arsenal. According to media reports both pro-al Shabaab and independent news outlets said that Kenyan forces have suffered heavy casualties however exact numbers of casualties from both sides could not be established at the time of reporting. Days following the attack the number of Kenyan dead is believed to be 100.

An IED exploded destroying a motor-cycle and killing its driver on the airport road (18km NW of Jowhar) on 15/01. The target is not clear but is assumed to be targeting an AMISOM convoy frequently used the road, though not present at the time.

A gunman from Marehan shot and killed another man from the same clan in Cabud Waaq in the morning of 15/01. The motive is reportedly a dispute over land ownership. The perpetrator escaped and no arrest was reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab attacked a group of Kenyan forces in Dhamase. Casualties of death and military equipment were reported on the Kenyan forces, specific numbers not known.
Unidentified attackers hurled a hand grenade against SNG police on foot patrol on Jamhuriya Road in the evening of 16/01. No causalities reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: An IED targeted a KDF convoy passing in Likooley Village (96km SW of Beled Xawo) in the afternoon of 16/01. One vehicle was reportedly destroyed while villagers also reported the sound of heavy gun-fire. Casualties are unknown.

Residents of Buuhoodle town staged anti-Somaliland rally on 16/01. The rally was aimed to express the locals' support to Khatumo forces following the takeover of Balli Cad Village by Somaliland forces. The protestors matched in the streets of the town chanting anti-Somaliland slogans. The rally was reportedly organized by the Khatumo administration led by its president. Key speakers at the rally called for attacks against Somaliland forces.
Al Shabaab sentenced two men to death and publicly executed them in a firing squad in Aw Dheegle Village (38km SW of Afgooye) on 16/01. The two men were accused of spying for SNG forces.

A gunman from Jejeele shot and injured a civilian man hailing from Galjecel in Hawl-Wadaag neighbourhood (Beled Weyne) in the evening of 16/01. The victim was reportedly trespassing a private farm belonging to the perpetrator. Elders of both sub-clans are trying to defuse the situation.

ACTOR2: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Suspected al Shabaab fighters raided a private house in Alwileh, Beled Xawo District (approx. 25km NW of Ceel Cadde), killing the owner of the house and allegedly four KDF soldiers who seek sanctuary in the house after the Ceel Cadde attack on 17/01. No other casualties were reported.

Unknown perpetrators shot and killed two SNG soldiers in Kuwait neighbourhood (Dharkenley District) in the night of 17/01. The motive is unknown and the perpetrators escaped. There are unconfirmed reports that the killers are members of a clan militia based in the area.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against a NISA security outpost in the livestock Market (Heliwa District) in the evening of 17/01. No casualties were reported.
Following a large scale attack and ultimate take-over of Ceel Cadde on 15/01, al Shabaab exits the city on 17/01. It is not clear if SNG or KDF forces have yet regained control of the town.

Armed militia from Galjeel opened fire at a private truck in Faranjibaley (approx. 5km W of Belet Weyn) and killed a man from Jejeele and injured another one. It is not clear if this incident is revenge for the shooting of a Galjeel man in a day earlier in Hawl-wadaag neighbourhood.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: KDF Military reportedly killed three civilians in a grazing area called Sanoe near Ceel Cadde (60km SW of Garbahaarey in the afternoon of 17/01. Reports indicate that KDF carried out security/search operation for its soldiers taken by al Shabaab fighters and reportedly killed three nomads herding their livestock.

A SNG soldier shot and killed a mini-bus driver in Siinka Dheer (14km SE of Afgooye) in the afternoon of 17/01. The motive behind the killing is reportedly a dispute over money extortion at a check point. No arrest was reported.
Unidentified helicopter shot and killed two herders near Xuliya Village (57km SE of Laas Qoray) on 17/01.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab forces shot and killed four AMISOM-KDF forces found hiding in a house near Ceel Cadde. The soldiers had apparently been in hiding following the attack on the city  on 15/01.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters attacked an SNG forces position in Rimaygacmeed (6km SE of Afgooye) on 18/01. Attackers withdrew and no casualties were reported.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against NISA forces in the vicinity of Barakat Cemetery (Yaaqshiid District) in night of 18/01. The attackers withdrew and no casualties were reported.

Reports indicate that an unknown warplane conducted air strikes against suspected al Shabaab position in Arabow village (47km NE of Bu'ale) in the afternoon of 18/01. Residents reports indicate that the targeted base was destroyed but no human casualties were reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Kenya defence forces (KDF) warplanes conducted airstrikes against al Shabaab in the vicinity of Ceel Cadde (55km SW of Garbahaarey) in the morning of 18/01. Reports Indicate that the airstrikes reportedly caused civilians' casualties and displacement of population. Included among the al Shabaab dead was senior leader Maalim Janow, the leader of the Abu Zubeir brigade. Exact total figures not known.

More than a hundred people staged an anti-Somaliland demonstration in Ceel-Buh Village (116km E of Ceerigaabo) on 18/01. The demonstrators were chanting anti-Somaliland slogans over unfulfilled developmental pledges made by Somaliland government to Warsangeli-inhabited areas. Unconfirmed reports indicate that anti-Somaliland politicians lobbying for the formation of regional state for Dhulbahante and Warsangeli sub-clans in Sanaag Region were behind the rally.
Unidentified attackers shot and killed a Quranic teacher in the outskirts of Bulo Burte town in the morning of 18/01. The motive is currently unknown and the perpetrators escaped.

Two groups of ISWA forces clashed in Diinsoor in the afternoon of 19/01. The clash was triggered after Diinsoor DC and ISWA local commander exchanged undisclosed heated argument and then the DC hit the commander using his vehicle followed by shootout between their escorts. One of the body guards of the DC was injured during the exchange of gunfire while the DC's vehicle was burnt after it was hit by bullet at the fuel tank. Ethiopian forces intervened and separated the two sides.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: An IED targeted AMISOM convoy on the road between Bulo Mareer and Gol-Weyn villages (28& 21km respectively) in the morning of 19/01 followed by an ambush from suspected al Shabaab fighters. AMISOM forces after a short brief of armed clash repulse the attackers. Casualties unknown.

Somaliland forces and Khatumo militia clashed in Kalabaydh Village (30km S of Laas Caanood) in the night of 19/01. The two sides used both light and heavy weapons during the clash which lasted for an hour after which the Khatumo forces withdrew. The attack was initiated by the Khatumo forces from Sahdheer (59km SW of Laas Caanood). Casualties could not be established.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against SNG forces based in Mushaani village (14km NW of Marka) in the morning of 19/01. The attackers withdrew immediately and no casualties were reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: KDF forces reached Ceel Gadde again on 19/01 after the al Shabaab attack. KDF forces concentrated on search operation but no IEDs were discovered. Al Shabaab fighters left the town already two days before and no armed clash was either reported. Kenyan forces were able to overtake the town.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Kenyan fighter jets have launched airstrikes in Ceel Gaduud and Dabley [southwestern Somalia] parts of Somalia in pursuit of Al-Shabab militants who killed Kenya Defence Forces [KDF] soldiers on 15/01. Date of the strikes not known - sources dated 19/01. No reported causalities.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Kenyan fighter jets have launched airstrikes in Ceel Gaduud and Dabley [southwestern Somalia] parts of Somalia in pursuit of Al-Shabab militants who killed Kenya Defence Forces [KDF] soldiers on 15/01. Date of the strikes not known - sources dated 19/01. No reported causalities.
Al Shabaab fighters executed an elderly man accused of being a witch-doctor in Kurtunwaarey in the afternoon of 19/01.
Unidentified clan militia attack an al Shabaab location in Adan Yabaal, Middle Shabeelle, killing six.
Al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against a SNGF defence post in Carbiska (5km SE of Afgooye) on 20/01. Attackers withdrew immediately and no casualties were reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Ethiopia)
NOTES: Suspected al Shabaab fighters attacked an ENDF convoy near Lanta Garaski (approx. 15km N of Waajid on 20/01. Attackers fired small arms fire against the convoy and escaped. ENDF continued with their journey to Buurdhuxunle. No reported causalities.

Two men, first suspected to be members of Jubaland security forces were executed by firing squad east of Jilib town on 20/01. The men who hail from Ogaden sub clan were caught on their way towards Kenya boarder with no exact area mentioned. None of the Jubaland force commanders admitted that the killed men were among Jubaland forces.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: Two people have been killed after Al-Shabaab fighters ambushed an African Union army convoy which later resulted in heavy fighting near the southern Somalia town of Buulo Mareer.

A group of al Shabaab fighters launched a complex attack against Seafood and Beach View restaurants on 21/01. The attack began with a VBIED explosion at the entrance of the restaurants followed by around five attackers entering the restaurants from the beach side and firing at customers. Security guards from the restaurants engaged the al Shabaab fighters in a gun-fire exchange before NISA and Gaashaan forces arrived and took over the operation. Roughly an hour later, a second explosion (a suspected VBIED) happened outside of the restaurants but causing no casualties as the place was already cleared by NISA. Between 22:45 and 23:10, around six explosions of hand grenades were reported. Reports indicate that more than 25 people including a national UN staff and six attackers were killed and more than 50 others, including a national INGO staff were wounded.

A group of al Shabaab fighters launched a complex attack against Seafood and Beach View restaurants on 21/01. The attack began with a VBIED explosion at the entrance of the restaurants followed by around five attackers entering the restaurants from the beach side and firing at customers. Security guards from the restaurants engaged the al Shabaab fighters in a gun-fire exchange before NISA and Gaashaan forces arrived and took over the operation. Roughly an hour later, a second explosion (a suspected VBIED) happened outside of the restaurants but causing no casualties as the place was already cleared by NISA. Between 22:45 and 23:10, around six explosions of hand grenades were reported. Reports indicate that more than 25 people including a national UN staff and six attackers were killed and more than 50 others, including a national INGO staff were wounded.

Local militia from Xawadle sub-clan attacked an al Shabaab position in Mabaax Village (75km E of Bulo Burte) on 21/01. Reports indicate that AMISOM/SNG forces reached the village after the clash however is not known if they will remain in there. One militia and two al Shabaab fighters were killed in the clash.

Khatumo forces reportedly carried out hit-and-run attacks against Somaliland forces based in Bali Cad and Widhwidh Villages (49km N and 51km E of Buuhoodle) in the night of 22/01. The Somaliland forces reportedly responded with both light and weaponry fire during the clash which lasted for an hour after which the Khatumo forces withdrew. Casualties could not be established.

Khatumo troops reportedly carried out hit-and-run attack against Somaliland forces based in Kalabaydh Village (30km S of Laas Caanood) in the night of 22/01. Somaliland forces reportedly responded with light and heavy weaponry fire during the clash which lasted for an hour after which the Khatumo forces withdrew. No causalities reported.

Khatumo forces reportedly carried out hit-and-run attacks against Somaliland forces based in Bali Cad and Widhwidh Villages (49km N and 51km E of Buuhoodle) in the night of 22/01. The Somaliland forces reportedly responded with both light and weaponry fire during the clash which lasted for an hour after which the Khatumo forces withdrew. Casualties could not be established.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: KDF conducted an airstrike in Ceel Gaduud (48km SW of Garbarhaarey) on 22/01. Casualties were unable to confirm. The target of the strike was not articulated by the source.

Locals reported that a missile hit a location outside Kananax Village (43km SE of Diinsor) on 22/01. It is not clear who and how the missile was fired as no noise of a plane was heard during the time. Casualties are unknown. The target of the shelling is not known, military or civilian.

Residents of Buuhoodle town staged anti-Somaliland rally on 16/01. The rally was aimed to express the locals' support for Khatumo forces following the takeover of Balli Cad Village by Somaliland forces. The protestors matched in the streets of Buuhoodle chanting anti-Somaliland slogans and burned the Somaliland flag. The rally was reportedly organized by the Khatumo administration led by its President.

More than a hundred Rahanweyn traders staged a peaceful demonstration in Ceerigaabo on 23/01. This follows after governor of Sanaag Region gave Rahanwayn traders a seven-day ultimatum to leave Ceerigaabo. The demonstrators requested Somaliland president to intervene and give them enough time to prepare for their exit.  Police dispersed the demonstrators. Reports six traders were arrested during the protest.

Two groups of SNG forces exchanged gun-fire in the vicinity of Ex-Control Afgooye (Dayniile Distrct) in the morning of 24/01. Reason behind the clash is said to be land dispute related between Habar-Gidir and Murusade. Both sides suffered casualties (numbers not known) while the situation is still tense.

Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a hit and run attack against SNGF position in Carbiska (5km SE of Afgooye) in the evening of 24/01. There was a brief exchange of gun-fire before the attackers withdrew. No casualties were reported.

A group of Ethiopian Oromo ethnic staged a peaceful demonstration in front of Somaliland ministry of Interior in Hargeisa on 24/01 in protest against new instructions issued by Somaliland government to deport Ethiopian national, mainly Oromos. The protestors requested from the government to reconsider the instructions and review the issue case by case while also asking for more time if the government fail to honour their request. Some protestors stated that they stayed in Somaliland over 40 years and owned assets. Police arrived at the scene and dispersed the demonstrators.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: KDF planes launched an airstrike against [al Shabaab locations] Daar Village (31km NW of Baardheere) on 24/01. Casualties are still unknown.
Unknown assailants shot and killed a SNGF soldier in Bundo Weyn in the evening of 24/01. The perpetrators managed to take his AK-47 and escaped from the scene.

Two groups from SNG police and ISWA forces clashed near ISWA presidential palace (Baidoa) in the morning of 25/01. The clash was allegedly triggered after SNG local police commander ordered some of ISWA military personnel to be disarmed because of their absenteeism in the military barracks while the military officers ignored prompting shootout. Two soldiers were killed while another one was injured.
Suspected al Shabaab fighters launched a brief hit and run attack against NISA troops in Biyo Degaanka on 25/01. Attackers withdrew immediately and no casualties were reported.

Al Shabaab fighters destroyed a donkey cart heading to Burdhuxunle in Lanta Garaski (15km N of Wajiid) on 25/01. The owner was badly beaten and warned against transporting goods to ENDF/SNGF. At the time of the incidents, the donkey was not carrying goods.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Ethiopia)
NOTES: Suspected al Shabaab fighters ambushed and attacked an ENDF convoy heading from Xudur to Tayeelow in Shiida Village (26km NE of Xudur) on 25/01. Attackers fired small arms and RPGs against the convoy but retreated immediately after ENDF/ISWA forces responded. No casualties were reported but one hut caught fire in the village after being hit by a round of RPG.

A group of people from southern Somalia staged a demonstration in front of the immigration office in Borama on 25/01. The group were protesting against the decision by the Somaliland government to expel all non-citizens. The protestors appealed to the government to reconsider its deportation decree. Police dispersed them and arrested five of them after they refused to leave the area.
Armed gunmen shot and killed a civilian man in the vicinity of Wajir neighbourhood (Marka) in the morning of 25/01. The motive is believed to be clan revenge. The victim hails from Biimaal clan.

Reports indicate that KDF troops withdrew from Ceel-Cadde Village (55km SW of Garbarhaarey) shortly after mid night on 26/01. Al Shabaab fighters took over the control of the town without any clash. The motive behind the withdrawal of KDF military is no clearly known, but thought to be military strategy.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: AMISOM forces leave Baadhaade on 26/01; al Shabaab quickly fills the void.

Unidentified men armed with pistols shot and killed a businessman in the medical section of Bakaara Market (Hawl-Wadaag District) in the afternoon of 26/01. The motive behind the killing is unknown and the perpetrators escaped.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Burundi)
NOTES: Unidentified attackers hurled a hand grenade against AMISOM (Burundians) base inside Kabka compound (Hodan District) in the evening of 26/01. The AMISOM forces responded with gunfire after the attack. No casualties were reported.
Unidentified attackers hurled a hand grenade against SNG forces on foot patrol near Biyo Degeenka (Hodan District) in the night of 26/01. No causalities.
SNG forces conducted a security operation in Safarnooleys Village (51km SE of Luuq) on 26/01. The forces captured a suspected al Shabaab fighter and beheaded him. No other casualties were reported.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighter ambushed a KDF convoy, travelling from Ceel Cadde to Likooley on 26/01. The attack was opened with an IED explosion and followed by an exchange of gun-fire. Unconfirmed reports indicate that two KDF vehicles were destroyed and the District Commissioner of Ceel Cadde, travelling with the convoy was seriously injured. Further reports indicate that the KDF convoy had to remain at the targeted place and did not arrive in Dhamase as expected.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: KDF helicopters bombed a grazing area approximately 20km NE of Hoosingow (Badhaadhe District) in the afternoon of 26/01. The area is inhabited by pastoralists and casualties are unknown. The specific target of the KDF is not known.

Somaliland army pulled out of Bali Cad Village (51km E of Buuhoodle) and established temporary base in the areas of Bali Hadhac (62km NE of Buuhoodle) on 26/01 for an undisclosed reason. The forces were initially part of the troops that recently took over the control of the village from Khatumo administration.

A gunman from Dashiishe shot and injured another man from Issa Mohamud in Tuurjaale neighbourhood (Bossaso) in the evening of 26/01. Reports indicate that the shooting followed after the perpetrator and the victim had physically assaulted each other for undisclosed reasons. The perpetrator escaped while the victim was taken to hospital.

A gunman hailing from Habar-Yunis/Ali Saciid sub-clan shot and killed a SPU officer in Burco in the afternoon of 26/01. The incident happened after a group of police officers including the victim went to stop a construction of a disputed plot of land. The perpetrator who claims the ownership of the disputed land was later arrested by the police.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: An IED hit a KDF convoy in Kolbiyow (33km SW of Badhaadhe) in the morning of 27/01. Initial reports indicate that one KDF was killed and nine others wounded while one APC was damaged. Helicopters from Kismaayo are said to have flown to the area to medevac the injured soldiers to Dhobley.

A magnetic IED attached to a vehicle exploded in the vicinity of Mogadishu Cinema (Wadajir/Medina District) in the afternoon of 27/01. The vehicle belonged to one of the military officers who was not in the car when the incident happened. Two civilian bystanders were slightly injured in the blast.

Gunmen reportedly hailing from Dhulbahante shot and killed a driver of a vehicle transporting khat in the outskirts of Hoosingo (97km NW of Badhaadhe) in the morning of 27/01. The victim hail from Sheekhal clan and the incident was reportedly related to previous revenge killings.

Local residents of Maydh (50km N of Ceerigaabo) held a peaceful demonstration on 27/01 in protest against the director of health in the region from Warsangeli. The protestors accused the director of diverting all health facilities to eastern Sanaag where his clan dominates and they called government to intervene the matter.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Kenyan forces kill an al Shabaab "commissioner" in the Likooleey area of Ceel Cadde. The commissioner may have been in the custody of the Kenyan military at the time of this death.

Jubaland intelligence forces shot and injured a poet from Darood/Ogaden sub-clan in Aargo - Fanoole Neighbourhood of Kismaayo  in the morning of 27/01. The man was reportedly shot after ignoring a stop order form the forces during an ongoing security operation.  He was hospitalized locally and later medevaced to Mogadishu.

Unidentified attackers armed with pistols shot and killed a custodial officer in the vicinity of Dabakaya Madow neighbourhood (Dharkenleey District) in the morning of 28/01. The victim was reportedly on his way to work when the incident happened. The perpetrators escaped.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: AMISOM/KDF reportedly withdrew from their base in Bula Gudud (32km NE of Kismaayo) in the afternoon of 28/01. Reports indicate that the KDF forces moved to Kismaayo and so far this is the third base Kenya forces vacated.  Further reports indicate that al Shabaab fighters immediately moved in to the village.
An anti-al Shabaab protest is held in Abdul-Aziz 28/01. The protest was a direct response to an attack on a Liido beach restaurant.

A group of al Shabaab fighters ambushed a SNG soldier in the vicinity of Abiikarow (13km NW of Marka) in the morning of 28/01. The soldier and another civilian man were driving a motorbike when the incident happened. The SNG soldier was killed and the civilian was injured in the ambush.

Dir clan militias attacked Xawadle forces in Deefow (29km NW of Belet Weyn) on 28/01. At least 1 Xawadle militiaman was killed and another one was injured. Casualties from Dir side are unknown. Both militias were concentrating in the vicinity of Deefoow and tensions remained high. Lieu police is also at the scene.

Jubaland intelligence force shot and injured a man from Darood/Marehan at Somalistar (Calanley neighbourhood) in Kismaayo on 28/01. The man was reportedly holding a black plastic pistol, and tried to run away after he saw the approaching forces. A stray bullet fired during the incident reportedly killed an intelligence officer (Darood/Ogaden) and injured a female civilian (Darood/Marehan).
Garowe residents staged a peaceful demonstration against 4.5 formula in Barhada square in the morning of 28/01.
Suspected al Shabaab gunmen attacked and injured a judge in Baardheere on the evening of 29/01.

National Intelligence and Security Agency (NISA) conducted a security operation targeting al Shabaab operatives in Ceelasha (12km SE of Afgooye) in the morning of 29/01. NISA captured unspecified number of al Shabaab fighters and seized weapons. One NISA soldier and one al Shabaab combatant were killed during a shootout, while the operation was ongoing.

A peaceful demonstration supporting the 4.5 formula for allocation of parliamentary seats took place in Baidoa town in the morning of 29/01. The demonstration was organized by the local administration.

A large number of people staged a peaceful demonstration in front of the mayor office's in Eyl on 29/04 in support of Puntland President's decision to oppose 4.5 formula. The mayor addressed the rally.
Unidentified attackers hurled a hand grenade against the residence of Baraawe DC in Baraawe town in 29/01. No casualties were reported. Perpetrators escaped.

Clan militias hailing from Majerteen/Wabeeneeye sub-clan and Warsangali/Dubeys sub-clan clashed in vicinity of Qaw village (16km W of Bosasso) on the afternoon of 30/01. The confrontation was linked to a land dispute and it lasted for about one hour. Casualties are unknown. Governor of Bari region and the regional police commissioner, supported by 10 technicals, reached the area to prevent further clashes. The situation remains tense.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-)
NOTES: A joint SNG/AMISOM operation yields 50 al Shabaab arrests in Jowhar.

A SNG soldier opened gunfire against a group of civilians in the vicinity of Via Ejito (Hamar Weyne area) on 30/01 for unknown reasons. The perpetrators escaped. Three civilians were injured in the shooting.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab clashes with AMISOM Kenyan forces in Baardheere. A "number" of Kenyan soldiers are said to have been killed and wounded in the ambush.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighters ambushed a KDF reconnaissance unit near Taraka village (approx. 47kms E of Baardheere) in the afternoon of 31/01. The KDF forces were assessing the road between Faafax Dhuun (approx. 26kms E of Taraka) and Taraka at the time of the attack. Casualties are unknown. Following the attack, KDF forces shelled Jungal (approx. 23kms E of Baardheere) and Taraka. The two incidents of shelling were locally perceived as indiscriminate. No reports about casualties of the shelling are currently available.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: Al Shabaab fighters ambushed a KDF reconnaissance unit near Taraka village (approx. 47kms E of Baardheere) in the afternoon of 31/01. The KDF forces were assessing the road between Faafax Dhuun (approx. 26kms E of Taraka) and Taraka at the time of the attack. Casualties are unknown. Following the attack, KDF forces shelled Jungal (approx. 23kms E of Baardheere) and Taraka. The two incidents of shelling were locally perceived as indiscriminate. No reports about casualties of the shelling are currently available.

A group of women and children from Daray Macaane staged a peaceful demonstration complaining about the piles of garbage which had been dumped in the area. The piles from the town had been dumped thus affecting the Hygienic situation of the area and caused many diseases to the area inhabitants. The police came to the scene and dispersed the gathering, there is no arrests or casualties reported.

A number of Renting Vehicle owners demonstrated in front of the governor's office venue complaining about the National Electoral Commission (NEC) renting regulation. Those drivers accusing the NEC of making the regulation difficult for those drivers to work in the NEC Registration Campaign. The NEC has made a condition for the renting vehicles in which new models for Land Cruisers 4X4 and should be in good condition and verified from a certain Garage which became a difficult to majority renting vehicle owners in the town.

Youth hailing form Habar Yonis and Habar Jeclo sub-clans fought in Barwaaqo neighbourhood (Ceerigaabo) on 31/01 following a dispute at a wedding ceremony. Ceerigaabo police intervened, shot in the air, and arrested 4 people from both sides.

Garowe central jail forces demonstrated over unpaid salaried and denied access to officials who tried to enter the jail on 31/01. The protesting forces stated that the protest will continue until the dispute is resolved. The central jail was built by UNODC for pirates during presidency of Abdirahman Farole.

Local taxi drivers staged a large demonstration in front of the local municipality and on the main Garowe tarmac road, halting businesses and traffic movements in Garowe in the morning of 31/01. The protest was a response to governments decision to ban local taxis from carrying khat sellers. The ban followed suspicions that alcohol is being smuggled together with khat. Unspecified number of protestors were arrested.

ACTOR1: AMISOM: African Union Mission in Somalia (2007-) (Kenya)
NOTES: SNFG soldiers, with strong support of AMISOM-KDF, conducted a large-scale house to house security operation in Baardheere town in the morning of 31/01. Reports indicate that about 100 suspects were arrested during the operation. The security operation followed the assassination attempt on Baardheere court judge.
Two alleged thieves were beaten, tied up and drowned in a dam in Marikana after they robbed a shop owned by a foreign national.
A man who ran over a child was subsequently beaten by the community outside Vereeniging.
Traffic came to a grinding halt on the main route into Durban as about 100 buses blocked off all the lanes in protest over payment for December.
Two factions of the ANC violently clash, throwing bottles and stones at each other. One group was marching about alleged corruption while the other faction sought to block the march.
Police fired smoke grenades to separate two ANC factions before they came to blows over a march against corruption in Rustenburg. The factions threw bottles and stones at each other and police.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: ANCYL: African National Congress Youth League
NOTES: Protesters, supported by the ANCYL, protested at th Durban Undersea Club on the beachfront.

A group of Kagiso residents protested. The protestors burnt two private vehicles and blocked several roads with burning tyres. When police arrived, they fired rubber bullets to disperse the crowd. No arrests or injuries were reported.
Supporters of the Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) tried to disrupt the symbolic handing over of houses in Marikana near Rustenburg in North West.

ANC regional secretary Tokyo Mataboge was assaulted by a group of ANC members allegedly sympathetic to Madibeng local municipality executive mayor Jostina Mothibe. The attack occurred during a meeting at a community hall in Brits on January 6

ALLY_ACTOR_1: ANCYL: African National Congress Youth League
NOTES: ANCYL marched outside the Standard Bank headquaters in Johannesburg to protest the racist remarks of an employee at the bank.

Police arrived to investigate proceedings at a kangeroo court. Angry residents however are alleged to have pelted police vans with stones. Police responded by firing live ammunition, shooting one person dead
A man who was fleeing an angry crowd was killed after he landed in front of a moving car near Umlazi in Durban.
2 men, alleged to have stolen two goats, were assaulted with sticks and fists and also pelted with stones while they attending the 'kangeroo' court proceedings.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: ANCYL: African National Congress Youth League
NOTES: About 300 people gathered at the entrance to the KwaZulu-Natal coastal resort town of Scottburgh ahead of a march against racism.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: EFFSC: Economic Freedom Fighters Students Command
NOTES: University of Pretoria students and workers disrupted registration during a protest against outsourcing. Led by the EFF Student Command, protesters vandalised the building and dumped rubbish on the floor.
Registration at Wits University was disrupted after students resumed picketing under their #FeesMustFall campaign at the campus.
Protesters have shut down the University of South Africa's (UNISA) Sunnyside Campus, expressing their dissatisfaction with management.
At the University of Johannesburg, a scene reminiscent of last year's protests played out as students and private security guards clashed outside the campus
CPUT students writing exams at Walter Sisulu University (WSU) were forced to stop after students from that institution started protesting for free education.

Community activists and parents at Austerville Primary School, in Wentworth, are calling for the sacking of the newly appointed principal. Protesters first took to the streets on Monday, demonstrating outside the school, and continued on Thursday.

Students and contract workers demonstrated outside the Univeristy in Pretoria and UNISA. However, they were met by aggressive police officers and soon found themselves on the wrong end of stun grenades; three workers sustained minor injuries
During the court appearances of 4 murder suspects, Farmers and ANC members hurled water bottles and rocks at one another. Police contained the situation.
Demonstrators took to the streets and spent the night burning tyres and branches on the road.
Private security guards allegadly used violence to remove students who were occupying building at Wits University

After the killing of Anwar Solomons, a group of about 50 residents went after his suspected killer and found him in a house. They began to assault him until a policeman came to his rescue, firing several shots in the air to disperse the crowd.
Hundreds of service delivery protesters in Chintsa East shut down the town's main access road to demand the municipality provide them with housing, water and electricity.
A group of 287 people have been arrested for throwing stones and damaging property at the Marabastad Home Affairs department.
Protesting students and outsourced workers at the University of Pretoria (UP) picketed outside campus
At Mfuleni Primary School, about 300 parents staged a sit-in, demanding that their children be placed.
Several people were arrested after municipal offices, a clinic and a fire station were set alight during violent service delivery protests in Waterval. These arrests likely took place after the riot.
Parents and community members blockaded the entrance of a school outside Robertson. During the protest, they chained the front gates, preventing any learners or staff from entering the premises.

Workers marched through the streets towards the TUT main campus. A cleaner at Protea Hotel had his wheelie bin taken from him and when he protested, he was attacked and chased inside the building. They were ordered to retreat and when they stood their ground, police opened fire, firing rubber bullets and tear gas into the crowd.
MyCiTi bus users protested in front of a bus stop in Tafelsig, Mitchells Plain, complaining it was of a poor standard, compared to those in other suburbs.
About 350 angry residents marched to the Port Elizabeth City Hall to demand an improvement in service delivery in their ward.
About 300 students protested outside a campus of the Thekwini College in Durban
The Cape Town Rastafarian community protested outside Woodstock Police Station.

Community activists and parents at Austerville Primary School, in Wentworth, are calling for the sacking of the newly appointed principal. Protesters first took to the streets on Monday, demonstrating outside the school, and continued on Thursday.
Parents staged a sit-in in attempts to enrol their children in the Mfuleni school.
Several people were arrested after municipal offices, a clinic and a fire station were set alight during violent service delivery protests in Waterval. These arrests likely took place after the riot.
Chanting DA members presented a memorandum of grievances outside the provincial legislature, demanding Fransman vacate his position as leader of the ANC in the province.
Unisa and the University of Pretoria remained closed as protests continued at the two institutions.
An angry crowds of ANC supporters protested and subseuqently ripped a giant #ZumaMustFall banner off the side of a building in Cape Town.
During a protests in Cape Town and the removal of the #ZumaMustFall poster, ANC supporters allegedly assaulted a civilian.
A man suspected of stealing a TV set was murdered during a vigilante attack in Bardale informal settlement in Mfuleni at the weekend.
At an ANC branch general meeting in Hammanskraal, women were apparently assualted by bouncers who burst into the venue. They said they had been slapped and dragged out of the meeting.
During ANC Branch Meetings in Gauteng, members were attacked in the towns of Winterveld and Bronkhorstspruit.
During ANC Branch Meetings in Gauteng, members were attacked in the towns of Winterveld and Bronkhorstspruit.
Protest action reportedly took place at the Acadia campus of TUTs. These protests are part of ongoing protests led by students and outsourced workers.

Hundreds of Ethiopians living in South Africa protested outside the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) in Johannesburg, demanding that African legislators help them intervene in stopping alleged human rights violations in Ethiopia.
At the University of Pretoria, petrol bombs were thrown at a truck at the university, causing minimal damages. The actions was part of ongoing protests at Universities throughout Pretoria.
A group of about 16 women stripped naked and stormed into the offices of the ANC in Pretoria, in protest over the events which took place on the 16th January 2016

ALLY_ACTOR_1: EFFSC: Economic Freedom Fighters Students Command
NOTES: At the UNISA  Sunningdale campus, protesters aligned to the EFF Student Command protested. A recycling bin was reportedly set alight during the protest.
A community leader was ambushed and beaten up in Philippi by residents.
More than 40 ANC members from ward 41 in Zwelitsha demonstrated outside the party's Dr WB Rubusane regional offices.
About 30 independent drivers for Coca-Cola staged a protest outside the Competition Tribunal in Pretoria.
Students and workers protesting at the University of Pretoria (UP), defying a court interdict that ordered them to be at least 150m away from the institution.
Parents demonstrated at the Avondale School in Atlantis. They are demanding the construction of a new building.
Protests broke out again on the National Highway next to Barcelona informal settlement. Residents are furious that portable and communal toilets haven't been cleaned for weeks.
Protesters took to the national highway (N2)  in Cape Town. The road was closed and some tires were allegedly burnt.
Animal activists in East London, supported by the East London Animal Warriors, have staged demonstrations before every performance at the Mclaren's circus.
Protesters demonstrated outside the Pietermaritzburg Magistrates Court where a man charged with the murder and dismemberment of a Maqongqo teenager appeared briefly.
A protest was held at Eskom's Megawatt Park head office in Sunninghill by the Democratic Alliance.
Hundreds of people, angry at the installation of prepaid meters, blocked roads and damaged infrastructure at an Eskom service centre in Zola last week.
Protests continued on the roads next to Barcelona. While police arrived there were no reports of contact between the protesting residents and the police.
A dispute over the allocation of government houses led to the N2 being temporarily shut after protesting residents blocked the road with burning tyres in Ethembeni, KwaDukuza.
Parents protested outside a school in Philippi. Approximately 200 parents, students and teachers stood outside the school gates forcing the school to shut down.
The admissions office at NMMU was temporarily shut down by about 25 students who staged a protest.
An angry mob has assaulted a lawyer at a South African courthouse where he represented two men accused of murdering a young girl.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: ANCYL: African National Congress Youth League
NOTES: ANC Youth League (ANCYL) members carrying bananas marched on the DA's headquarters in Gardens yesterday, burnt the provincial ruling party's flag and an effigy of Penny Sparrow.

Hundreds of angry pupils and their parents attacked a Limpopo circuit office. Pupils and parents threw stones, broke down the gate, and smashed windows at the local circuit office, forcing employees to flee. No one was injured during the violence.

Tshwane Metro Police officers fired rubber bullets at protesters outside of Tshwane Mayor Kgosientso Ramokgopa's parents home in Atteridgeville in Pretoria. Tyres were set alight, bricks were also packed in the road and protesters threatened to burn down Ramokgopa's own home.

At least 500 people protested in Kempton Park, Johannesbury after a Nigerian man was killed while in police custody. Police respnded with by firing stun grenades and rubber bullets at protesters. Several people were injured during the incident.
A police officer was accidently killed by an angry community, during a funeral, when he was mistaken for being a criminal.

Two men were shot dead in Inchanga. Although the motives are unknown, there is speculation that the killings were politically motivated. Five others were injured, 10 cars were damaged, and tyres were slashed.
An ANC councillor was assaulted by angry community members, leaving him with head wounds and a broken finger.
Some residents of Kagiso went on a rampage in protests against their removal to a new area where the government planned to build RDP houses for them.
The Walter Sisulu Universitys Butterworth campus was shut down following renewed protest action.
At the Mahikeng campus of the North West Univesity, the campus was disrupted by protesting students.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: EFFSC: Economic Freedom Fighters Students Command
NOTES: Workers continued to protest at the Tshwane University of Technology (TUT) in pursuit of their demands under the banner of #OutsourcingMustFall.
A group of about 70 residents marched to the home of Buffalo City Metro councillor in Mdantsane Township.
In Lenasia, parents and pupils have protested the racism of the principal.
Protests continued as protesters clashed with police in Kagiso. Nine people were arrested during the clashes. The rioters were demanding RDP houses.
Residents of an  informal settlement, near Lenasia, blocked streets with bricks and burning tyres in protest against poor service delivery.
Mentally and physically-disabled UCT students spoke out about their exclusion and feelings of alienation on campus at a peaceful protest held at UCT.

In Lusikisiki, protests turned ugly as residents allegedly stoned vehicles and houses. Police intervened in which residents responded by hurling stones at the 20-strong police. Reports of injuries have been noted, including the injury of a ward counciller.
Masiphumelele High School learners boycotted school and instead marched to the Department of Education in Fish Hoek.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: EFFSC: Economic Freedom Fighters Students Command
NOTES: Protesters forced Tuts University to remain closed in ongoing fees protests.
Protests entered a third day in Kagiso. During the events, a police vechile drove over a man, killing him. The rioters were demanding RDP houses from the government.

Farm evictions in Paarl turned violent when workers pelted the police with stones to prevent them from evicting two families at the Lynquedoch farm. One person was reportedly injured, while several others were arrested.

Several hundred residents of a Durban hotel went on the rampage. Residents barricaded the road with burning tyres and rubbish bins and when police tried to control the crowd, protesters threw stones at them and looted shops.
Eskom workers, supported by NUM and NUMSA, embarked on a work stoppage protest in in Booysens, Pretoria.

A 5000-strong crowd marched on the police station from two directions. As tensions flared, community members, who were not part of the mob, were also pelted with rocks. Police shot rubber bullets and tear gas at the demonstrators.

Protesters, including workers and students, gathered at Tuts University in ongoing fees protests. Following, these protesters were attacked by SASCO members who emerged with bricks and bottles, which they began to throw at the workers who were sitting down. One worker was injured and was bleeding heavily.
Following the attack on protesters, police opened fire with rubber bullets and stun grenades to disperse the violent groups.
Thousands of DA supporters marched for jobs in the Johannesburg CBD.
About 10 students, believed to be members of the Stellenbosch Fees Must Fall movement, protested outside the Admin building of Stellenbosch Univeristy.
More than 100 disgruntled residents protested outside the East London City Hall demanding electricity connections and the removal of their ward councillor.
Residents gathered in Lusikisiki in continuing protests over the appoitment of a local councillor. Residents gathered and blocked the road but there are no reports of violence or arrests.

ALLY_ACTOR_1: EFFSC: Economic Freedom Fighters Students Command

Outside the land claims court in Randburg, Johannesburg, protesters wearing green Afra T-shirts protested and waved placard to highlight the lack of land reform.
Chaos erupted at an annual meeting in Port Elizabeth when rugby officials fought their way past security officials and disrupted the meeting in protest.

At a SACP event in Turfloop in Limpopo, ANC members allegedly disrupted the meeting, collapsing the marquee in which the meeting was being held, disconnecting the power supply and switching off the sound system.

Land Invaders protested at a site in Etwatwa, many of whom were EFF members. During negotiations between police and land invaders, Red Ants official arrived and began to destroy temporary homes without consulting or discussing the issue with anyone. This prompted the land invaders to charge at the Red Ants with sticks. The situation was diffused before it could degenerate into more violence.
In Mthatha, a man was killed, three people were severely injured and three houses were torched when residents took revenge on suspected gang members after the killing of a 19-year old taxi driver.
Clashes between military and Arrow Boys militia in Yambio.

ACTOR1: Military Forces of Tunisia (2014-) National Guard
NOTES: Security forces in Tunisia have killed an Algerian combatant during an operation in the mountains near Kesra, Siliana governorate. National Guard units shot an armed man between Mount Serj and Mount Ballouta in Siliana province on Sunday.

Clashes were reported near the border post of Hazoua, in Tozeur governorate. A group of demonstrators shut down the post demanding to be recruited in the municipality. Police intervened firing teargas to disperse the crowd, which in turn triggered the reaction of the protesters who started throwing stones on police.
